title: Serialize/Table-normalized
description: AST-only mode rebuilds merged cells in trailing form and orders the pseudo rows
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

`|>|Cell9 |` becomes `|Cell9 |<|`, and the caption row moves directly below
the class row: the grid emitter rebuilds merges in trailing form and emits
the pseudo rows in canonical order.

Why: the AST records colspan and rowspan as cell attributes and moves the
caption container to the front for DOM validity; which side the merge
marker sat on and where the caption row stood are not recorded, so the
emitter re-derives the grid with trailing `<` cells, `~` rowspan markers
and the class, caption, body, footer row order.

* Covers: serializeFromTree in $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/table.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
